cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.DS 

This paper proposes a general predictor for integrating multi-view information for machine learning tasks. The paper discusses the use of laboratory results for disease diagnosis as an example, which suggests a potential application in the medical field. The paper also mentions the use of different loss functions, indicating a focus on machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as these sub-categories are also relevant to the integration of multi-view information and machine learning.
